---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const faqData = [
  {
    question: "Are Costco hot dogs all beef?",
    answer: "Yes. Costco hot dogs are 100% USDA Choice beef with no fillers, poultry, or pork."
  },
  {
    question: "What grade of beef does Costco use?",
    answer: "Costco hot dogs are made with USDA Choice beef, which is a high-quality grade."
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Are Costco Hot Dogs All Beef?"
  description="Yes — Costco hot dogs are 100% all-beef USDA Choice. No fillers, no pork, no poultry."
  type="faq"
  faqData={faqData}
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-8 text-center mb-10">
      <p class="text-sm text-green-700 font-medium uppercase tracking-wide">Answer</p>
      <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-green-800 mt-2">Yes</p>
      <p class="text-green-700 mt-2">100% USDA Choice beef</p>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Are Costco Hot Dogs All Beef?</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">A definitive answer with full ingredient transparency.</p>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">USDA Choice Beef</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Costco hot dogs are made from 100% USDA Choice beef. This is a high-quality grade of beef with good marbling and excellent flavor. Unlike many budget hot dogs that use a blend of meats and fillers, Costco's commitment to pure beef sets it apart.</p>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">What's NOT in Them</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Costco hot dogs contain no poultry, no pork, no mechanically separated meat, and no fillers like soy protein or textured vegetable protein. The ingredient list is refreshingly short: beef, water, salt, and minimal preservatives.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
